commit.message: fix another strdup() on unterminated input in  mapi_attr.c
drop redundant null terminator - already set by xcalloc

allow the memory limits to be respected strictly

this relaxes the memory limit check, so one byte extra
may be allowed, after the check vs the limit the user sets.

fix shift into sign bit

The intermediate uint8 is implicitly promoted to an int before shifting,
shifting into the sign bit is undefined behaviour in C.

The compiler does not seem to exploit this, for gcc at least, the
generated code is identical.

fix strdup() on possibly unterminated string

Otherwise, a buffer read overflow may happen at
file.c line 236

I had forgotten to update the version number when I made my new year
release. So now I have to update the version number for real this

The intention of the assertion is to ensure there is at least enough
bytes left for the GUID (16 bytes). If the input buffer is exactly 16
that should be valid as well...
